// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/preprocess/p08/pass.test — P8 `#include` search-path
// resolution per `docs/spec/nsl_pp.ebnf` notes section + the contract
// topic table in
// `specs/002-m1-lex-preprocess/contracts/preprocessor-seam.contract.md`.
//
// Topic per the table: "`#include "f"` resolves via `-I`;
// `#include <f>` resolves via `NSL_INCLUDE`".
//
// Two search forms (P8):
//   * Quote form `#include "widget.nsl"`  → searched in (1) directory
//     of including file, (2) every `-I <dir>` argument, in
//     registration order. **`-I` is consulted ONLY for quote-form**.
//   * Angle form `#include <gadget.nsl>`  → searched in every
//     `NSL_INCLUDE` colon-separated path entry. **`-I` is NOT
//     consulted for angle-form**.
//
// Auxiliary files live under `Inputs/quote/` and `Inputs/angle/`,
// which lit excludes from auto-discovery (test/lit.cfg.py
// `config.excludes`). The driving `pass.test` is what lit runs.
//
// Pass shape: each include file declares a unique reg name
// (`quote_marker` and `angle_marker`); both names cross the seam
// after the preprocessor splices the include contents.
//
// Tasks.md T044. **NOTE per agent brief**: T044 will run RED until
// the parallel `nsl-frontend-impl` agent's T061 wires the
// `-I`/`NSL_INCLUDE` flags through to `lib/Driver/EmitTokens.cpp`'s
// `Preprocessor` (currently the flags are accepted but ignored —
// see `lib/Driver/EmitTokens.cpp` `(void)opts.include_paths`).

// We point `-I` at the quote-form Inputs directory and pre-populate
// `NSL_INCLUDE` with the angle-form Inputs directory. Both forms
// then resolve from disjoint search roots.
//
// %S is lit's expansion to the directory containing this .test
// file (so `%S/Inputs/quote` is the absolute path to the
// quote-search root regardless of where lit was invoked).

// RUN: echo '#include "widget.nsl"' >  %t.nsl
// RUN: echo '#include <gadget.nsl>' >> %t.nsl
// RUN: env NSL_INCLUDE=%S/Inputs/angle %nslc -I %S/Inputs/quote -emit=tokens %t.nsl | FileCheck %s

// Plain (non-NEXT) check directives below tolerate intervening
// tk_line_directive markers, which the preprocessor emits at each
// #include enter/return per P13.
// CHECK:      tk_reg{{[ \t]+}}reg
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_identifier{{[ \t]+}}quote_marker
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_semicolon{{[ \t]+}};
// CHECK:      tk_reg{{[ \t]+}}reg
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_identifier{{[ \t]+}}angle_marker
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_semicolon{{[ \t]+}};

// Neither `#include` directive crosses the seam (P12 boundary):
// CHECK-NOT: tk_identifier{{[ \t]+}}include
